Below is an instruction that describes a task. Write a response that appropriately completes the request.

### Instruction:
create a javascript function that uses regex to extract a three character code like "1Jn" from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm".  The characters can be upper or lower case letters or digits. And the filename extension must be ".usfm".

### Response:

Here's an example of how you could create a JavaScript function that uses regular expressions to extract a three-character code from a file name in format "57-1Jn.usfm":
```javascript
function getCode(filename) {
  const regex = /[0-9]+-\w{3}/g; // matches any combination of digits and lowercase letters followed by exactly three characters

  if (regex.test(filename)) {
    return filename.match(regex)[0]; // returns the matched substring
  } else {
    console.log("Invalid file name format.");
    return null;
  }
}
```
To use this function, you would call it with a string representing your file name as an argument:
```javascript
const filename = "57-1Jn.usfm"; // replace with actual file name
const code = getCode(filename);
console.log("Extracted code:", code);
``` 
This would output the extracted three-character code, which in this case is "1Jn".
